                     "uuid": "1df98dc5-523f-42ae-9a69-3e9410849ebb",
                     "text": "Hossenfelder, Sabine",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "cd738b4d-32bd-4ea6-8aef-6653d961de19",
                     "text": "Hossenfelder, Sabine",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2021",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "76b636be-45db-4e52-8ecd-5c873344f926",
                     "text": "Lincoln, Don - Fermilab",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### Limits of Science\n\nPhrases like \"scientific results are just theories\" are common, leading us to a reflection:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 3: On Knowledge</b><br /><br />Does this statement reveal limited understanding of science?</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "Dismissing findings as \"just theory\" reflects a fundamental misunderstanding of scientific methodology. Science doesn't seek absolute truths or aim to replace beliefs, but rather pursues continuous knowledge expansion. Skepticism drives progress - we daily test and refine scientific theories. When limitations emerge, we develop more comprehensive models while recognizing previous theories remain valid within their original parameters.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_game",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>The game</h3>To facilitate understanding of the scientific method, History Tracers developed an interactive game applying the method to various scenarios. Access it: <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('96f3d3af-15c3-4c37-9d0e-e4b7db0db1db'); return false;\">Scientific Method</a>.</p><p>We recommend completing at least the <b>\"Training\"</b> levels when prompted by the text for deeper methodological understanding.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_conclusion",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Conclusion\n\nThis text introduced the scientific method used throughout History Tracers. While imperfect, this method's greatest strength is its openness - it never restricts the pursuit of new knowledge.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
